What IS Default in EKS

EKS Created
    │
    ├── Node Group        ✅ Created
    ├── ASG               ✅ Created automatically
    ├── Min/Max/Desired   ✅ Set by you
    ├── EC2 Health check  ✅ Default
    │
    ├── Cluster Autoscaler ❌ NOT installed
    ├── Karpenter          ❌ NOT installed
    └── HPA                ❌ NOT installed
------------------------------------------------------
🔵 Full Picture
-----------------------------------------------------
Helm Install      → Karpenter controller running
      +
NodePool          → What instances to launch
      +                (type, size, limits)
EC2NodeClass      → Where to launch
                     (subnet, security group, AMI)
      │
      ▼
Pod Pending → Karpenter scales node ✅
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 AWS Console View
---------------------------------
Node Group Scaling Configuration
──────────────────────────────────
Minimum size    →  2  nodes
Desired size    →  3  nodes
Maximum size    →  6  nodes

But it does not increase node to max if more pod is pending we need to install Karpenter

Helm installs Karpenter     → Just installs the tool ✅
NodePool + EC2NodeClass     → Tells Karpenter WHAT and HOW to scale ✅

Without NodePool            → Karpenter sits idle ❌
                            → No nodes added ever ❌

KARPENTER
═══════════════════════════════════════════

WHY KARPENTER OVER CLUSTER AUTOSCALER
═══════════════════════════════════════════

Cluster Autoscaler          Karpenter
──────────────────          ──────────────────
Slow (2-3 minutes)    vs    Fast (seconds)
Works with ASG        vs    Directly EC2
Limited instance type vs    Any instance type
Old approach          vs    Modern approach
Complex config        vs    Simple config

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 1 - SET ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
═══════════════════════════════════════════

export CLUSTER_NAME=my-cluster
export AWS_REGION=ap-south-1
export AWS_ACCOUNT_ID=$(aws sts get-caller-identity \
  --query Account --output text)

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 2 - CREATE IAM POLICY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

cat > karpenter-policy.json <<EOF
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ec2:CreateLaunchTemplate",
        "ec2:CreateFleet",
        "ec2:RunInstances",
        "ec2:CreateTags",
        "ec2:TerminateInstances",
        "ec2:DescribeLaunchTemplates",
        "ec2:DescribeInstances",
        "ec2:DescribeSecurityGroups",
        "ec2:DescribeSubnets",
        "ec2:DescribeInstanceTypes",
        "ec2:DescribeAvailabilityZones",
        "iam:PassRole",
        "ssm:GetParameter"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
EOF

aws iam create-policy \
  --policy-name KarpenterPolicy \
  --policy-document file://karpenter-policy.json

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 3 - INSTALL KARPENTER CRDs
═══════════════════════════════════════════

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aws/karpenter/main/pkg/apis/crds/karpenter.sh_nodepools.yaml

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aws/karpenter/main/pkg/apis/crds/karpenter.k8s.aws_ec2nodeclasses.yaml

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 4 - DEPLOY KARPENTER
═══════════════════════════════════════════

cat > karpenter-deployment.yaml <<EOF
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: karpenter
  namespace: karpenter
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: karpenter
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: karpenter
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: controller
          image: public.ecr.aws/karpenter/controller:v0.33.0
          env:
            - name: CLUSTER_NAME
              value: my-cluster
            - name: AWS_REGION
              value: ap-south-1
          resources:
            requests:
              cpu: "1"
              memory: "1Gi"
            limits:
              cpu: "1"
              memory: "1Gi"
EOF

kubectl create namespace karpenter
kubectl apply -f karpenter-deployment.yaml

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 5 - CREATE NODEPOOL
═══════════════════════════════════════════

cat > nodepool.yaml <<EOF
apiVersion: karpenter.sh/v1beta1
kind: NodePool
metadata:
  name: default
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      requirements:
        - key: kubernetes.io/arch
          operator: In
          values: ["amd64"]
        - key: karpenter.sh/capacity-type
          operator: In
          values: ["on-demand"]
        - key: node.kubernetes.io/instance-type
          operator: In
          values: ["t3.medium", "t3.large", "t3.xlarge"]
      nodeClassRef:
        name: default
  limits:
    cpu: 100                     # Max total CPU across all nodes
    memory: 100Gi                # Max total Memory
  disruption:
    consolidationPolicy: WhenUnderutilized
    consolidateAfter: 30s        # Remove idle nodes after 30s
EOF

kubectl apply -f nodepool.yaml

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 6 - CREATE EC2NODECLASS
═══════════════════════════════════════════

cat > nodeclass.yaml <<EOF
apiVersion: karpenter.k8s.aws/v1beta1
kind: EC2NodeClass
metadata:
  name: default
spec:
  amiFamily: AL2
  role: KarpenterNodeRole
  subnetSelectorTerms:
    - tags:
        karpenter.sh/discovery: my-cluster
  securityGroupSelectorTerms:
    - tags:
        karpenter.sh/discovery: my-cluster
EOF

kubectl apply -f nodeclass.yaml

───────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 7 - VERIFY KARPENTER
═══════════════════════════════════════════

# Check karpenter pods
kubectl get pods -n karpenter

# Check nodepool
kubectl get nodepool

# Check logs
kubectl logs -n karpenter \
  -l app=karpenter -f

