HOW KARPENTER WORKS
═══════════════════════════════════════════

Pod Pending (no resources)
        │
        ▼
Karpenter detects pending pod
        │
        ▼
Checks pod requirements
(CPU, Memory, Node selector)
        │
        ▼
Launches right EC2 instance
directly in seconds ✅
        │
        ▼
Pod scheduled ✅

Load drops
        │
        ▼
Karpenter consolidates nodes
Terminates idle nodes ✅
Cost saved ✅

───────────────────────────────────────────

SUMMARY
═══════════════════════════════════════════

Step 1 → Set env variables
Step 2 → Create IAM role
Step 3 → Install CRDs
Step 4 → Deploy Karpenter
Step 5 → Create NodePool
Step 6 → Create EC2NodeClass
Step 7 → Verify ✅

NOTE:
- Karpenter = Best choice for Production
- Faster, smarter, cheaper than Cluster Autoscaler
- Uses NodePool instead of ASG
- Always set CPU and Memory limits in NodePool
